<item>
            <title>[LU-9021] Clarify whether RHEL/CentOS 6.8 is supported</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9021</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Even though &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8838&quot; title=&quot;kernel update [RHEL6.8 2.6.32-642.11.1.el6]&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-8838&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-8838&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is listed as part of the features of 2.9, RHEL6.8 is not listed on the support matrix for 2.9 and the RPMs appear to be missing from the download site.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://wiki.hpdd.intel.com/display/PUB/Changelog+2.9&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://wiki.hpdd.intel.com/display/PUB/Changelog+2.9&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Has Lustre support for the 6.x series been dropped?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>RedHat and CentOS</environment>
        <key id="43004">LU-9021</key>
            <summary>Clarify whether RHEL/CentOS 6.8 is supported</summary>
                <type id="9" iconUrl="https://jira.whamcloud.com/images/icons/issuetypes/undefined.png">Question/Request</type>
