                                    <version>Lustre 2.9.0</version>
                                                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>2</watches>
                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="180884" author="pjones" created="Sun, 15 Jan 2017 18:16:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;.. however, I will also add that there are users out there who do use distros that are not officially supported and a posting to the lustre-discuss mailing list may mean some people speak up to confirm that they have been using this combination even though it falls outside of the offical test matrix for the release.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="180883" author="pjones" created="Sun, 15 Jan 2017 13:26:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Lana&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Yes support for RHEL 6.x has been offically dropped on the latest community releases and the focus is instead on RHEL 7.x&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
